						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying before the Bhadrakāḷi temple at Āraṅgipēṭa.</p>						

						<p>Eastern Gaṅga: Chōḍagaṅgadēva, 5th year.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1003, Uttarāyaṇa-Saṅkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 5 <hi rend="italic">māḍas</hi> to the god Vishṇudēva of Gāra, for burning a perpetual lamp by Bramiya-Bōya, son of Eṟi-Bōya. The maintenance of the lamp was entrusted to the Maṅājanas.</p>						

						</summary>
